Math.Set

Class Set

  • java.lang.Object
    • Math.Set.Set
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Math.MathObject

    public class Set
extends java.lang.Object
implements Math.MathObject
    The class that represents Sets in mathamatics. This one also includes a lot of different functions that are utilized in Statistics.

        public Set(EquationSystem pEq)
        Creates a Set based off the EquationSystem eq. Passes -10, 10, 25 to another constructor as the min, max, and cStep (the cardinality of the Set).
        Parameters:
        pEq - The EquationSystem that the Set will be based off of.

      • Set

        public Set(EquationSystem pEq,
           double min,
           double max,
           double cStep)
        Creates a Set based off the EquationSystem eq.
        The arr1 of the Set is defined by the code: int pos = 0; for(double i = min; i < max; i += (max - min) / cStep, pos++) arr1[pos] = i;
        The arr2 of the Set is defined by the code: int pos = 0; for(double i = min; i < max; i += (max - min) / cStep, pos++) arr2[pos] = pred(i, equationsys);
        Parameters:
        pEq - The EquationSystem that the Set will be based off of.
        min - The starting value for arr1.
        max - The ending value for arr1.
        cStep - The step size for arr1.
        See Also:
        pred(double,EquationSystem)

      • pred

        public static double pred(double pVal,
                          EquationSystem pEq,
                          java.lang.String toSolve)
        Predicts the estimated value of the "yhat" using the the EquationSystem pEq. Passes a ArrayList of Equations of length 1 to EquationSystem's eval function, with the first element in the Arraylist being instantiated by the following code:
        new ArrayList<Equation>() {{ add(new Equation(toSolve + " = " +pVal));}}
        Parameters:
        pVal - The value to set "y" to when evaluating the EquationSystem pEq.
        pEq - The EquationSystem that will be evaluated with "yhat" being set to pVal.
